DUBAI: This Ramadan, a number of brands have curated limited-edition beauty boxes primed for the holy season. Whether you’re seeking an update to your makeup bag or a gift for a loved one (Ramadan is the month of giving after all), here is a roundup of some of the top beauty boxes available. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle Namshi  Priced at $108, this beauty box is designed as a calendar and is filled to the brim with skincare, makeup, and haircare essentials. Huda Beauty  During the countdown to Eid, open a door a day in this beauty calendar to unveil some of Huda Beauty and Wishful’s best-selling products. It retails for $142. YSL  This luxurious satin-finish gift box includes a limited-edition perfume and candle and can be purchased at Bloomingdales for $490. It would make a thoughtful gift for the hostess at an iftar gathering. Sephora  Inside the limited-edition box, designed by award-winning Saudi artist Fida Al-Hussan, there are seven must-have beauty items from Sephora’s best-selling brands including benefit and Tarte for $49. Look Fantastic  From night balms to purifying cleansers, stay perfectly pampered all the way to Eid and beyond with this beauty box from Look Fantastic. You can purchase it online for $122. L’Occitane  An Eid calendar bursting with 6 of L’Occitane’s best-selling fragrances, bath, body, skincare, and hand care products with an affordable price tag of $30. 